race.comment: Terrific race with plenty of win chances. TACITO (5) has been good in two runs for the new local yard, the latest a close-up third here at 1200m. Fitter and extra trip a plus. Looks ready to fire. EEVALINA (9) was having first run for the new yard over 1100m here last time and wasn't far away. Has speed and over the extra ground will give a sight. WILD IMAGINATION (1) is a veteran mare who won with a massive weight last time, continuing the good run of SA trainer David Page. This mare is a stakes winner in SA and competitive in all the country cups around a mile so won't worry about the 1400m today. Big weight again but hard to knock. DEBONNAIRE (3) is fitter for two runs back but has two wins from three tries third-up and should be ready to fire. DADIRRA (8) is flying at the moment, including a last start win at the course and distance when leading throughout. Take catching again.
